Now you can say “switch to sonnet” instead of typing the full model path. Small
quality-of-life improvement that adds up over hundreds of interactions.
Internal Hooks for Logging and Memory
Beyond external webhooks, OpenClaw supports internal hooks that fire on system
events:
{
"agents": {
"defaults": {
"models": {
"anthropic/claude-opus-4-6": { "alias": "opus" },
"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5": { "alias": "sonnet-4-5" },
"openai-codex/codex-5.2": { "alias": "codex" }
}
}
}
}
